definitions.definition: A principal , low-level cloud type in the form of a gray layer with a rather uniform base , usually not associated with precipitation , and capable of producing corona phenomena and a weak, uniform luminance ; abbreviated S t .

main_definition: ( meteorology ) A principal , low-level cloud type in the form of a gray layer with a rather uniform base , usually not associated with precipitation , and capable of producing corona phenomena and a weak, uniform luminance ; abbreviated S t .
